Satanists Don’t Believe in Satan?

What if I told you I was a Christian who didn’t believe in Christ?  Or a 
scientist who didn’t believe in science?   Or a humanist who didn’t believe 
in humans? Most rational people would immediately see through that sort of 
duplicity.

And yet the reasonable convention of nomenclature is departed from 
regarding Satanism.  I have been told, time and again, by self-styled 
atheists, that those extremists who take upon themselves his name, on the 
one hand, also deny his existence, on the other.  

Jesus, the Truth, warned His followers to be utterly transparent and 
completely honest regarding their allegiance to Him, even in the face of 
persecution or loss of life:

"Whosoever shall confess me before men, him will I confess also before my 
Father which is in heaven.  But whosoever shall deny me before men, him 
will I also deny before my Father which is in heaven.  Think not that I am 
come to send peace on earth: I came not to send peace, but a sword.”  Mt 
10:32-34 

The sword Jesus brings is for division, not bloodshed.  One of my earliest 
instructors in Christ used to say, “The name of Jesus polarizes a crowd.”

The works of a Christian likewise are to be apparent and not hidden:

"Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and 
glorify your Father which is in heaven."   Mt 5:16

Conversely, Satan, who was a liar and a man-slayer from the beginning, 
makes no such demands upon his followers.  Secret allegiances, rituals, and 
worship are acceptable and will be rewarded. His followers need not speak 
truthfully, only expediently, since ”…there is no truth in him (Satan). 
 When he lies, he speaks his native language, for he is a liar and the 
father of lies.” Jn. 8:44  

The reason authentic Satanists need not be burdened by telling the truth is 
understandable and obvious.  Even to acknowledge his existence is to 
validate the Bible  —awkward!   And even in our increasingly irreligious 
and permissive society there remains a stigma upon —well, upon worshiping 
devils.   A hint of allegiance to Satan also polarizes a crowd.  Rightly so.

Satan’s work, we know from Scripture, is to steal, kill and destroy.  Jn. 
10:10 Whatever the works of Satanists may be, they have remained largely 
covert since the official Church was founded in the 1960s.  But what sort 
of works can be expected from a secretive subculture whose seventh and 
first (of nine) statements of belief are, respectively, that ”…man is just 
another animal… the most vicious animal of all”, and that “(mankind should 
engage in) indulgence instead of abstinence”?

What can be the fruit of a philosophy that demotes human beings to the 
status of beasts (—as does atheistic evolution and modern Scientism, also 
called Scientific Naturalism—) and simultaneously goads them on to 
unmitigated indulgence?  I wonder why those militant atheists who so often 
rail against Christianity and the Bible never do so against Satanists and 
the Satanic Bible.

When people tell us that Satanists don’t believe in Satan, they may be 
revealing more about themselves than Satanism.  Namely, their gullibility 
and willingness to believe the most logically absurd propositions, or else, 
their secret allegiance to that "great dragon… that old serpent… which 
deceiveth the whole world."  Rev 12:9  ﻿
